-- Mitsubishi May Build Solar Plant in Japan With Chubu Electric
-- B y   C h i s a k i   W a t a n a b e
-- 2013-01-15T02:50:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-15/mitsubishi-may-build-solar-plant-in-japan-with-chubu-electric.html
Mitsubishi Corp. (8058) ,  Japan ’s largest
trading house by market value, may build a solar power station
with  Chubu Electric Power Co. (9502)  in central Japan.  Mitsubishi and C-Tech Corp., a clean energy and
telecommunications unit of Chubu Electric, are considering
building a solar plant in Aichi prefecture, Takashi Shiwaku, a
Mitsubishi spokesman said by phone today. Aichi is home to
Toyota Motor Corp.’s head office in Toyota city.  The Nikkei newspaper reported Jan. 12 the companies will
build a 77 megawatt station in Aichi at a total cost of more
than 20 billion yen ($223 million). The paper did not say where
it got the information. Shiwaku said the capacity and the
location of the plant haven’t been decided.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chisaki Watanabe in Tokyo at 
